  "text": "We now study the effectiveness of integrating our methods with spam detection. To that end, we first use as a reference comparison a common spam removal method denoted here SpamRm [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Specifically, we apply Waterloo's spam detector [CITATION_3] upon the initial ranking, top to bottom, and remove documents d with a nonspam score, N onSpam(d), below 50 until we accumulate 1000 documents; N onSpam(d) is in [0, 100] and reflects the presumed percentage of documents in the entire ClueWeb English collection (category A, which includes around 500 million documents) that are \"spammier\" than d.",
